00305 static int rna_Scene_object_bases_lookup_string(PointerRNA *ptr, const char *key, PointerRNA *r_ptr)
00306 {
00307     Scene *scene = (Scene*)ptr->data;
00308     Base *base;
00309 
00310     for (base = scene->base.first; base; base = base->next) {
00311         if (strncmp(base->object->id.name+2, key, sizeof(base->object->id.name)-2) == 0) {
00312             *r_ptr = rna_pointer_inherit_refine(ptr, &RNA_ObjectBase, base);
00313             return TRUE;
00314         }
00315     }
00316 
00317     return FALSE;
00318 }

00328 static Base *rna_Scene_object_link(Scene *scene, bContext *C, ReportList *reports, Object *ob)
00329 {
00330     Scene *scene_act = CTX_data_scene(C);
00331     Base *base;
00332 
00333     if (object_in_scene(ob, scene)) {
00334         BKE_reportf(reports, RPT_ERROR, "Object \"%s\" is already in scene \"%s\"", ob->id.name+2, scene->id.name+2);
00335         return NULL;
00336     }
00337 
00338     base = scene_add_base(scene, ob);
00339     id_us_plus(&ob->id);
00340 
00341     /* this is similar to what object_add_type and add_object do */
00342     base->lay = scene->lay;
00343 
00344     /* when linking to an inactive scene don't touch the layer */
00345     if (scene == scene_act)
00346         ob->lay = base->lay;
00347 
00348     ob->recalc |= OB_RECALC_OB|OB_RECALC_DATA|OB_RECALC_TIME;
00349 
00350     /* slows down importers too much, run scene.update() */
00351     /* DAG_scene_sort(G.main, scene); */
00352 
00353     WM_main_add_notifier(NC_SCENE|ND_OB_ACTIVE, scene);
00354 
00355     return base;
00356 }

00358 static void rna_Scene_object_unlink(Scene *scene, ReportList *reports, Object *ob)
00359 {
00360     Base *base = object_in_scene(ob, scene);
00361     if (!base) {
00362         BKE_reportf(reports, RPT_ERROR, "Object '%s' is not in this scene '%s'", ob->id.name+2, scene->id.name+2);
00363         return;
00364     }
00365     if (base == scene->basact && ob->mode != OB_MODE_OBJECT) {
00366         BKE_reportf(reports, RPT_ERROR, "Object '%s' must be in 'Object Mode' to unlink", ob->id.name+2);
00367         return;
00368     }
00369     if (scene->basact == base) {
00370         scene->basact = NULL;
00371     }
00372 
00373     BLI_remlink(&scene->base, base);
00374     MEM_freeN(base);
00375 
00376     ob->id.us--;
00377 
00378     /* needed otherwise the depgraph will contain freed objects which can crash, see [#20958] */
00379     DAG_scene_sort(G.main, scene);
00380     DAG_ids_flush_update(G.main, 0);
00381 
00382     WM_main_add_notifier(NC_SCENE|ND_OB_ACTIVE, scene);
00383 }

00485 static void rna_Scene_start_frame_set(PointerRNA *ptr, int value)
00486 {
00487     Scene *data = (Scene*)ptr->data;
00488     /* MINFRAME not MINAFRAME, since some output formats can't taken negative frames */
00489     CLAMP(value, MINFRAME, MAXFRAME);
00490     data->r.sfra = value;
00491 
00492     if (data->r.sfra >= data->r.efra) {
00493         data->r.efra = MIN2(data->r.sfra, MAXFRAME);
00494     }
00495 }

00508 static void rna_Scene_use_preview_range_set(PointerRNA *ptr, int value)
00509 {
00510     Scene *data = (Scene*)ptr->data;
00511     
00512     if (value) {
00513         /* copy range from scene if not set before */
00514         if ((data->r.psfra == data->r.pefra) && (data->r.psfra == 0)) {
00515             data->r.psfra = data->r.sfra;
00516             data->r.pefra = data->r.efra;
00517         }
00518         
00519         data->r.flag |= SCER_PRV_RANGE;
00520     }
00521     else
00522         data->r.flag &= ~SCER_PRV_RANGE;
00523 }

00526 static void rna_Scene_preview_range_start_frame_set(PointerRNA *ptr, int value)

00529

00532         /* set end of preview range to end frame, then clamp as per normal */

00534         data->r.pefra = data->r.efra;

00537     /* now set normally */

00542 static void rna_Scene_preview_range_end_frame_set(PointerRNA *ptr, int value)

00547     if ((data->r.flag & SCER_PRV_RANGE) == 0) {

00549         /* TODO: or just refuse to set instead? */
00550         data->r.psfra = data->r.sfra;

00666 static void rna_ImageFormatSettings_file_format_set(PointerRNA *ptr, int value)
00667 {
00668     ImageFormatData *imf = (ImageFormatData *)ptr->data;
00669     ID *id = ptr->id.data;
00670     const char is_render = (id && GS(id->name) == ID_SCE);
00671     /* see note below on why this is */
00672     const char chan_flag = BKE_imtype_valid_channels(imf->imtype) | (is_render ? IMA_CHAN_FLAG_BW : 0);
00673 
00674     imf->imtype = value;
00675 
00676     /* ensure depth and color settings match */
00677     if ( ((imf->planes == R_IMF_PLANES_BW) &&   !(chan_flag & IMA_CHAN_FLAG_BW)) ||
00678          ((imf->planes == R_IMF_PLANES_RGBA) && !(chan_flag & IMA_CHAN_FLAG_ALPHA)))
00679     {
00680         imf->planes = R_IMF_PLANES_RGB;
00681     }
00682 
00683     /* ensure usable depth */
00684     {
00685         const int depth_ok = BKE_imtype_valid_depths(imf->imtype);
00686         if ((imf->depth & depth_ok) == 0) {
00687             /* set first available depth */
00688             char depth_ls[] = {R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_32,
00689                               R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_24,
00690                               R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_16,
00691                               R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_12,
00692                               R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_8,
00693                               R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_1,
00694                               0};
00695             int i;
00696 
00697             for (i = 0; depth_ls[i]; i++) {
00698                 if (depth_ok & depth_ls[i]) {
00699                     imf->depth = depth_ls[i];
00700                     break;
00701                 }
00702             }
00703         }
00704     }
00705 
00706     if (id && GS(id->name) == ID_SCE) {
00707         Scene *scene = ptr->id.data;
00708         RenderData *rd = &scene->r;
00709 #ifdef WITH_FFMPEG
00710         ffmpeg_verify_image_type(rd, imf);
00711 #endif
00712 #ifdef WITH_QUICKTIME
00713         quicktime_verify_image_type(rd, imf);
00714 #endif
00715         (void)rd;
00716     }
00717 }

00731 static EnumPropertyItem *rna_ImageFormatSettings_color_mode_itemf(bContext *C, PointerRNA *ptr,
00732                                                                   PropertyRNA *UNUSED(prop), int *free)
00733 {
00734     ImageFormatData *imf = (ImageFormatData *)ptr->data;
00735     ID *id = ptr->id.data;
00736     const char is_render = (id && GS(id->name) == ID_SCE);
00737 
00738     /* note, we need to act differently for render
00739      * where 'BW' will force greyscale even if the output format writes
00740      * as RGBA, this is age old blender convention and not sure how useful
00741      * it really is but keep it for now - campbell */
00742     char chan_flag = BKE_imtype_valid_channels(imf->imtype) | (is_render ? IMA_CHAN_FLAG_BW : 0);
00743 
00744 #ifdef WITH_FFMPEG
00745     /* a WAY more crappy case than B&W flag: depending on codec, file format MIGHT support
00746      * alpha channel. for example MPEG format with h264 codec can't do alpha channel, but
00747      * the same MPEG format with QTRLE codec can easily handle alpga channel.
00748      * not sure how to deal with such cases in a nicer way (sergey) */
00749     if (is_render) {
00750         Scene *scene = ptr->id.data;
00751         RenderData *rd = &scene->r;
00752 
00753         if (ffmpeg_alpha_channel_supported(rd))
00754             chan_flag |= IMA_CHAN_FLAG_ALPHA;
00755     }
00756 #endif
00757 
00758     if (chan_flag == (IMA_CHAN_FLAG_BW|IMA_CHAN_FLAG_RGB|IMA_CHAN_FLAG_ALPHA)) {
00759         return image_color_mode_items;
00760     }
00761     else {
00762         int totitem = 0;
00763         EnumPropertyItem *item = NULL;
00764 
00765         if (chan_flag & IMA_CHAN_FLAG_BW)    RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, &IMAGE_COLOR_MODE_BW);
00766         if (chan_flag & IMA_CHAN_FLAG_RGB)   RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, &IMAGE_COLOR_MODE_RGB);
00767         if (chan_flag & IMA_CHAN_FLAG_ALPHA) RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, &IMAGE_COLOR_MODE_RGBA);
00768 
00769         RNA_enum_item_end(&item, &totitem);
00770         *free = 1;
00771 
00772         return item;
00773     }
00774 }
00775 
00776 static EnumPropertyItem *rna_ImageFormatSettings_color_depth_itemf(bContext *C, PointerRNA *ptr,
00777                                                                   PropertyRNA *UNUSED(prop), int *free)
00778 {
00779     ImageFormatData *imf = (ImageFormatData *)ptr->data;
00780 
00781     if (imf == NULL) {
00782         return image_color_depth_items;
00783     }
00784     else {
00785         const int depth_ok = BKE_imtype_valid_depths(imf->imtype);
00786         const int is_float = ELEM3(imf->imtype, R_IMF_IMTYPE_RADHDR, R_IMF_IMTYPE_OPENEXR, R_IMF_IMTYPE_MULTILAYER);
00787 
00788         EnumPropertyItem *item_8bit =  &image_color_depth_items[0];
00789         EnumPropertyItem *item_12bit = &image_color_depth_items[1];
00790         EnumPropertyItem *item_16bit = &image_color_depth_items[2];
00791         EnumPropertyItem *item_32bit = &image_color_depth_items[3];
00792 
00793         int totitem = 0;
00794         EnumPropertyItem *item = NULL;
00795         EnumPropertyItem tmp = {0, "", 0, "", ""};
00796 
00797         if (depth_ok & R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_8) {
00798             RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, item_8bit);
00799         }
00800 
00801         if (depth_ok & R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_12) {
00802             RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, item_12bit);
00803         }
00804 
00805         if (depth_ok & R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_16) {
00806             if (is_float) {
00807                 tmp = *item_16bit;
00808                 tmp.name = "Float (Half)";
00809                 RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, &tmp);
00810             }
00811             else {
00812                 RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, item_16bit);
00813             }
00814         }
00815 
00816         if (depth_ok & R_IMF_CHAN_DEPTH_32) {
00817             if (is_float) {
00818                 tmp = *item_32bit;
00819                 tmp.name = "Float (Full)";
00820                 RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, &tmp);
00821             }
00822             else {
00823                 RNA_enum_item_add(&item, &totitem, item_32bit);
00824             }
00825         }
00826 
00827         RNA_enum_item_end(&item, &totitem);
00828         *free = 1;
00829 
00830         return item;
00831     }
00832 }

01072 static void rna_RenderSettings_color_management_update(Main *bmain, Scene *UNUSED(scene), PointerRNA *ptr)
01073 {
01074     /* reset image nodes */
01075     Scene *scene = (Scene*)ptr->id.data;
01076     bNodeTree *ntree = scene->nodetree;
01077     bNode *node;
01078     
01079     if (ntree && scene->use_nodes) {
01080         /* XXX images are freed here, stop render and preview threads, until Image is threadsafe */
01081         WM_jobs_stop_all(bmain->wm.first);
01082         
01083         for (node = ntree->nodes.first; node; node = node->next) {
01084             if (ELEM(node->type, CMP_NODE_VIEWER, CMP_NODE_IMAGE)) {
01085                 ED_node_changed_update(&scene->id, node);
01086                 WM_main_add_notifier(NC_NODE|NA_EDITED, node);
01087                 
01088                 if (node->type == CMP_NODE_IMAGE)
01089                     BKE_image_signal((Image *)node->id, NULL, IMA_SIGNAL_FREE);
01090             }
01091         }
01092     }
01093 
01094     rna_Scene_glsl_update(bmain, scene, ptr);
01095 }

01113         }
01114     }
01115 }

01207 static void object_simplify_update(Object *ob)
01208 {
01209     ModifierData *md;
01210     ParticleSystem *psys;
01211 
01212     for (md = ob->modifiers.first; md; md = md->next)
01213         if (ELEM3(md->type, eModifierType_Subsurf, eModifierType_Multires, eModifierType_ParticleSystem))
01214             ob->recalc |= OB_RECALC_DATA|PSYS_RECALC_CHILD;
01215 
01216     for (psys = ob->particlesystem.first; psys; psys = psys->next)
01217         psys->recalc |= PSYS_RECALC_CHILD;
01218     
01219     if (ob->dup_group) {
01220         GroupObject *gob;
01221 
01222         for (gob = ob->dup_group->gobject.first; gob; gob = gob->next)
01223             object_simplify_update(gob->ob);
01224     }
01225 }

03899 /* scene.objects */
03900 static void rna_def_scene_objects(BlenderRNA *brna, PropertyRNA *cprop)
03901 {
03902     StructRNA *srna;
03903     PropertyRNA *prop;
03904 
03905     FunctionRNA *func;
03906     PropertyRNA *parm;
03907     
03908     RNA_def_property_srna(cprop, "SceneObjects");
03909     srna = RNA_def_struct(brna, "SceneObjects", NULL);
03910     RNA_def_struct_sdna(srna, "Scene");
03911     RNA_def_struct_ui_text(srna, "Scene Objects", "Collection of scene objects");
03912 
03913     func = RNA_def_function(srna, "link", "rna_Scene_object_link");
03914     RNA_def_function_ui_description(func, "Link object to scene, run scene.update() after");
03915     RNA_def_function_flag(func, FUNC_USE_CONTEXT|FUNC_USE_REPORTS);
03916     parm = RNA_def_pointer(func, "object", "Object", "", "Object to add to scene");
03917     RNA_def_property_flag(parm, PROP_REQUIRED|PROP_NEVER_NULL);
03918     parm = RNA_def_pointer(func, "base", "ObjectBase", "", "The newly created base");
03919     RNA_def_function_return(func, parm);
03920 
03921     func = RNA_def_function(srna, "unlink", "rna_Scene_object_unlink");
03922     RNA_def_function_ui_description(func, "Unlink object from scene");
03923     RNA_def_function_flag(func, FUNC_USE_REPORTS);
03924     parm = RNA_def_pointer(func, "object", "Object", "", "Object to remove from scene");
03925     RNA_def_property_flag(parm, PROP_REQUIRED|PROP_NEVER_NULL);
03926 
03927     prop = RNA_def_property(srna, "active", PROP_POINTER, PROP_NONE);
03928     RNA_def_property_struct_type(prop, "Object");
03929     RNA_def_property_pointer_funcs(prop, "rna_Scene_active_object_get", "rna_Scene_active_object_set", NULL, NULL);
03930     RNA_def_property_flag(prop, PROP_EDITABLE|PROP_NEVER_UNLINK);
03931     RNA_def_property_ui_text(prop, "Active Object", "Active object for this scene");
03932     /* Could call: ED_base_object_activate(C, scene->basact);
03933      * but would be a bad level call and it seems the notifier is enough */
03934     RNA_def_property_update(prop, NC_SCENE|ND_OB_ACTIVE, NULL);
03935 }
